    </div>

    <!-- Key Tax Considerations -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold font-heading mb-5" style="color: #1C1C1E;">Key Tax Considerations for Bergen County Residents &amp; Businesses</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Bergen County's tax environment is shaped by several intersecting forces that make working with a knowledgeable local CPA — one who understands both federal tax law and New Jersey's often divergent rules — genuinely valuable.</p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold font-heading mb-3 mt-6" style="color: #1C1C1E;">New Jersey State Income Tax</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">New Jersey imposes a progressive state income tax with rates ranging from 1.4% to 10.75% — one of the highest top marginal rates in the nation. For Bergen County residents with six-figure incomes, NJ income tax alone can represent tens of thousands of dollars annually. Year-round tax planning strategies — retirement contributions, pass-through entity elections, business deduction optimization — are essential for minimizing this burden legally.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Importantly, New Jersey does not conform to all federal tax law. The state does not allow the federal Section 199A Qualified Business Income (QBI) deduction on NJ returns. It has its own depreciation rules that differ from federal bonus depreciation and Section 179 expensing. These differences mean that a strategy that reduces your federal taxable income may not produce the same savings on your NJ return — and vice versa. A CPA who only understands federal rules can leave significant NJ tax savings on the table.</p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold font-heading mb-3 mt-6" style="color: #1C1C1E;">NYC Nonresident Income Tax for Commuters</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">A significant portion of Bergen County's working population commutes into New York City. These residents are subject to New York State nonresident income tax on their New York-sourced wages. While New Jersey provides a credit for taxes paid to other states, the credit calculation is not always straightforward, and proper planning — especially around work-from-home days, which can affect the allocation of wages between NJ and NY — is critical. The NYC commuter filing obligation has grown more complex in the remote work era, and many Bergen County residents are underplanning in this area.</p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold font-heading mb-3 mt-6" style="color: #1C1C1E;">New Jersey Property Tax</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">New Jersey has among the highest effective property tax rates in the nation, and Bergen County is among the more expensive counties in the state. Many homeowners find that their combined NJ property tax and state income tax routinely exceed the federal $10,000 SALT deduction cap established by the 2017 Tax Cuts and Jobs Act — meaning they're effectively unable to deduct a significant portion of their state and local taxes on their federal return. Business owners have a powerful workaround through the NJ Business Alternative Income Tax (BAIT) election for pass-through entities, which allows entity-level payment of NJ income tax that is fully deductible as a federal business expense, bypassing the SALT cap.</p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold font-heading mb-3 mt-6" style="color: #1C1C1E;">Estate Planning and Wealth Transfer</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">New Jersey eliminated its state estate tax in 2018, but the federal estate tax exemption is scheduled to drop significantly after 2025 under the TCJA sunset provisions. Bergen County's high-net-worth households need to be proactive about trust structures, gifting strategies, and business succession planning well before any legislative changes take effect.</p>

    <!-- ProAxis Serves All of Bergen County -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold font-heading mb-5 mt-10" style="color: #1C1C1E;">ProAxis Serves All of Bergen County</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">Our virtual CPA model means that geographic distance is never a barrier to getting expert service. We work with clients from every corner of Bergen County. Our primary service communities include:</p>
    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-8">
      {[
        { name: "Hackensack", slug: "hackensack" },
        { name: "Paramus", slug: "paramus" },
        { name: "Fort Lee", slug: "fort-lee" },
        { name: "Ridgewood", slug: "ridgewood" },
        { name: "Teaneck", slug: "teaneck" },
